@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
}
skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    BorderColor #6C757D
}
skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
    DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF3CD
    DiamondBorderColor #856404
}
skinparam swimlane {
    BorderColor #6C757D
    TitleBackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    TitleFontColor #212529
}
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #E8F4F8
skinparam NoteBorderColor #5B9BD5

title Lyra Checkpoint Download & Conversion\n<size:11><i>scripts/download_lyra_checkpoints.py</i></size>

|CLI|
start
:parse_args()
**--checkpoint_dir** (default: "checkpoints");

|main()|
:Set **ORG_NAME** = 'nvidia'
Set **extra_models** = \[\] (empty list);
:Create **checkpoints_dir**
Path(args.checkpoint_dir).mkdir(parents=True);
:Configure download:
  model_name = 'Lyra'
  repo_id = 'nvidia/Lyra'
  local_dir = checkpoints_dir/Lyra
  allow_patterns = \['lyra_static.pt', 'lyra_dynamic.pt'\];

|get_md5_checksum()|
:Collect **expected_files** from MD5_CHECKSUM_LOOKUP
where key starts with 'Lyra/';

note right
  MD5 Registry:
  Lyra/lyra_static.pt  → 28ddd050...
  Lyra/lyra_dynamic.pt → 91c1b392...
end note

if (expected_files list is empty?) then (yes)
  :Check if model_dir exists\nand is non-empty;
  if (model_dir exists & non-empty?) then (yes)
    :Return **True**\n(treat as verified);
  else (no)
    :Return **False**\n(download required);
  endif
else (no)
  :Iterate over each expected file;
  if (file exists on disk?) then (no)
    :Return **False**\n(file missing);
  else (yes)
    :Compute **hashlib.md5(file)**
    read in 8 KB chunks;
    if (computed MD5 == stored hash?) then (no)
      :Return **False**\n(checksum mismatch);
    else (yes)
      :Continue to next file;
      :All files verified;
      :Return **True**\n(checksums match);
    endif
  endif
endif

|main()|
if (checksum check returned False?) then (yes — download needed)
  :local_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True);
  |HuggingFace Hub|
  :snapshot_download(
    repo_id = 'nvidia/Lyra'
    local_dir = checkpoints_dir/Lyra
    allow_patterns = \['lyra_static.pt',
                       'lyra_dynamic.pt'\]
    local_dir_use_symlinks = False
  );
  |main()|
  :**lyra_static.pt** + **lyra_dynamic.pt**
  saved to checkpoints_dir/Lyra;
else (no — skip download)
  :Files already verified\n(checksums matched — skip);
endif

note right
  extra_models = \[\] — loop body
  never executes in current config
end note

stop

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
' Utility: convert_pixtral_checkpoint (standalone)
' Not invoked by main() — available for direct use
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

|convert_pixtral_checkpoint()|
note
  <b>Utility Function — not called from main()</b>
  Inputs: checkpoint_dir, checkpoint_name, vit_type
end note

start
:Resolve **save_dir** = checkpoint_dir/checkpoint_name
Resolve **save_path** = save_dir/model.pt;

if (save_path exists and size > 0?) then (yes)
  :Print "already exists"
  **Early return (idempotent)**;
  stop
else (no)
  :Resolve **pixtral_ckpt_dir** = checkpoint_dir/Pixtral-12B-2409
  os.makedirs(pixtral_ckpt_dir);
  |HuggingFace Hub|
  :snapshot_download(
    repo_id = 'mistralai/Pixtral-12B-2409'
    allow_patterns = \['params.json',
                       'consolidated.safetensors'\]
    local_dir = pixtral_ckpt_dir
  );
  |convert_pixtral_checkpoint()|
  :Set **dtype** = torch.bfloat16
  torch.set_default_dtype(bfloat16);
  :Glob **\*.safetensors** in pixtral_ckpt_dir
  Assert exactly 1 file found;
  :Load checkpoint via **safetensors.load_file()**;
  :Split checkpoint into sub-dicts:
  • **vit_ckpt** — keys with prefix 'vision_encoder.'
  • **projector_ckpt** — keys with prefix 'vision_language_adapter.'
  • **llm_ckpt** — all remaining keys;
  :Rename projector keys:
  w_in → projector.0
  w_out → projector.2;
  :Assemble **vlm_ckpt**:
  llm keys  → 'model.*'
  projector → 'mm_projector.*'
  vit keys  → 'vision_encoder.*';
  :Load **params.json** → pixtral_config;
  :Extract **vision_encoder_config**
  from pixtral_config\['vision_encoder'\];
  if (vision_encoder_config matches\nhardcoded vit_config\n(dim=1024, 24 layers, 16 heads)?) then (no)
    :Raise **AssertionError**\n(config mismatch);
    stop
  else (yes)
    :Build **llm_config** from pixtral_config:
    rename hidden_dim → ffn_hidden_size
    set vision_encoder = vit_type;
    :torch.save(\{
      'model': vlm_ckpt,
      'mm_projector': projector_ckpt,
      'vision_encoder': vit_ckpt
    \}, save_path);
    :Write **config.json** (llm_config) to save_dir;
    :Restore original dtype
    torch.set_default_dtype(orig_dtype);
    :shutil.rmtree(pixtral_ckpt_dir)
    **Cleanup original Pixtral download**;
    stop
  endif
endif

@enduml
